<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 19 at 10:29PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A cluster of strong thunderstorm will impact portions of
northeastern Vance and northern Warren Counties through 1115 PM
EDT...
At 1028 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Boydton, or 14 miles southeast of Chase City, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Warrenton, Norlina, Macon, Tungsten, Drewry, Bullocksville, Kerr
Lake, Lake Gaston, Wise and Southpointe And Morningstar Marinas.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
